---
filenames:
  # *.log (not *) so a future rotated authelia.log.1 / .gz in this dir is NOT fed to the
  # authelia parser (which would error on compressed/rotated content). Today only
  # authelia.log exists, so this is behaviour-preserving + future-proof.
  - /var/log/authelia/*.log
labels:
  type: authelia
---
# AppSec Component — inline L7 WAF. Traefik's bouncer plugin forwards each request here
# (crowdsecAppsecHost=crowdsec:7422) BEFORE proxying to the backend, so a malicious payload (a CVE
# exploit string, SQLi/SSTI, path traversal) is blocked on its FIRST request — the stream-mode
# ban-list only bans an IP AFTER enough log lines accumulate, so a first-hit payload sailed through.
# appsec_config crowdsecurity/appsec-default loads the virtual-patching (CVE signatures) +
# generic-rules inband rulesets installed via the crowdsec COLLECTIONS env (appsec-virtual-patching
# + appsec-generic-rules — deliberately NOT the full OWASP CRS, which is false-positive-prone).
# Bound 0.0.0.0 so traefik reaches it over the shared `proxy` net (NOT host-published — this port is
# internal). The plugin is set crowdsecAppsecUnreachableBlock:false (config.yml.j2), so an appsec
# broker hiccup fails OPEN — the edge keeps serving (deferring to the stream-mode ban-list) rather
# than 500ing the whole fleet; the appsec add-on must not become a new edge SPOF.
source: appsec
listen_addr: 0.0.0.0:7422
appsec_config: crowdsecurity/appsec-default
name: traefik-appsec
labels:
  type: appsec
